text: Intel Core i9 (codename: Skylake) is a name that Intel uses for the computer processors it makes for desktop and laptop computers. It part of the Intel Core series of processors. They are Intel's highest-end consumer CPU line. They can have a Cache of 17-25 MB, 12-18 Cores and 24-36 Threads, depending on the processor. == References == Category:Intel Core processors
title: Intel Core i9
